not be entitled to acquire any shares of the target company for a period of six months after completion of the open offer except pursuant to another voluntary open offer:
Provided that such restriction shall not prohibit the acquirer from making a competing offer upon any other person making an open offer for acquiring shares of the target company.
(3)Shares acquired through bonus issue or stock splits shall not be considered for purposes of the dis-entitlement set out in this regulation.
